2.00	Tom_Hall_(American_football)	Tom Hall (American football)	Thomas Francis Hall (born April 3, 1940 in Wilmington, Delaware) is a former American football wide receiver who played in the National Football League. He played eight seasons for the Detroit Lions (1962–1963), the Minnesota Vikings (1964–1966, 1968–1969), and the New Orleans Saints (1967). He played college football at the University of Minnesota.	
